SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 25
BY SENATOR FESI
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates the LIFTOff Louisiana Team in
developing a highly successful response to the Federal Aviation Administration's request for
proposals for the Electric Vertical Takeoff and Landing and Advanced Air Mobility Aircraft
Integration Pilot Program.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend the "LIFTOff Louisiana" team led by the Department of Transportation and
3 Development's office of multimodal commerce with key support from the Houma-
4 Terrebonne Airport Commission and the Gulf of America Center of Excellence
5 (UGC) for Large-Unmanned Aircraft Systems, and their many partners for their roles
6 in developing a highly successful response to the Federal Aviation Administration's
7 (FAA) request for proposals for the Electric Vertical Takeoff and Landing and
8 Advanced Air Mobility Aircraft Integration Pilot Program.
9 WHEREAS, the LIFTOff Louisiana team has worked and will continue to work with
10 public and private partners under the guidance of the FAA on a range of specific projects
11 while adhering to high aviation safety standards; and
12 WHEREAS, the team and their partners will demonstrate advances in aviation
13 technological capabilities and operational concepts; and
14 WHEREAS, the LIFTOff Louisiana team seeks to advance ambitious national
15 priorities in key areas that serve the public interest, including piloted and unmanned
16 approaches to air mobility, research and development, emergency management services,
17 medical transportation, and novel technologies supporting offshore logistics operations; and
18 WHEREAS, the team's initiatives demonstrate broad public benefits, including
